This paper discusses the performance of evolutionary algorithms (EAs), which are commonly used in the field of computational intelligence and optimization. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper involves theoretical analysis of the algorithms, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses the convergence rate and hitting time of the algorithms, which could place it in the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.SE (Software Engineering).
